<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10144h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10144h">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10144h"> 144(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cringe</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;So, too, with King Water. The rushing water perchance swallows in death your loved first-born, drowned perhaps in a canoe or crossing a rickety bridge. Yea, he, King Water, is the murderer of your darling, but darest thou refuse to drink him? Contrariwise, at sundown you <mark>cringingly</mark> kneel with your cup and&mdash;and drink of your son&apos;s murderer! Hail, King Water! and hail, King Fire though ye slay me, yet must I cling to you.&rdquo; <small> Daniel Crawford, <a name="DCTB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DCTB"><cite title="source">Thinking Black</cite></a> (1912) 159</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
